The Chronicle Showbiz Correspondent
Actress, poet and musician Lady Tshawe has shown off her baby bump in a series of stunning photos displaying her glow and that she is ready for motherhood. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-503596" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF-680x680.jpeg" alt="" width="680" height="680" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF-680x680.jpeg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF-80x80.jpeg 80w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF-360x360.jpeg 360w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF-50x50.jpeg 50w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF-200x200.jpeg 200w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF-100x100.jpeg 100w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/370B713F-B28E-4FD4-8545-C44EC0C73ABF.jpeg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
The artiste has been under the radar for the better part of this year and with the baby bump pictures shows why. Lady Tshawe (real name Nomashawekazi Damasane), looks all but ready to welcome her bundle of joy with husband Thembalethu Jinkila Ndlovu. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-503607" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/8CFAAC03-6B66-474C-8184-30E46ED5ED54.png" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/8CFAAC03-6B66-474C-8184-30E46ED5ED54.png 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/8CFAAC03-6B66-474C-8184-30E46ED5ED54-360x200.png 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
“She is fierce! Imbokodo! Ndlovukazi! Mpangazitha! Yimi lo uQhube. Your NdebeleCrush,” is what Lady Tshawe wrote on her Facebook page, while wearing a black long-sleeved maternity dress which was completed by a bright yellow blazer. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-503609" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/EB99C74C-CB0D-4146-A143-E3F26AD5E038.png" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/EB99C74C-CB0D-4146-A143-E3F26AD5E038.png 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/EB99C74C-CB0D-4146-A143-E3F26AD5E038-360x200.png 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> <img class="alignnone size-article-featured-image wp-image-503611" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/0B62E5D7-5D19-4C3F-9530-314827D5AF8E-680x380.png" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/0B62E5D7-5D19-4C3F-9530-314827D5AF8E-680x380.png 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/07/0B62E5D7-5D19-4C3F-9530-314827D5AF8E-360x200.png 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />